  "texts": [
    "As a starting point, let us consider the well-studied case (see, e.g., [49][50][51][52][53][54]) of a single charge carrier moving in the ferromagnetic background (short FM) of the localized spins [see Fig. 1(a)], thus an initial state of the form:|Ψ 0,F ⟩ = |k 0 = π/2, ↑⟩ c ⊗ |FM⟩ f.(2)In this exactly solvable case [50][51][52] of effectively two particles -electron and one emitted magnon -the system relaxes, yet evidently not to a thermal state, as evidenced by the persistence of finite-momentum peaks in the quasi-momentum distribution.",
    "Likewise, for the case of two charge carriers in a ferromagnetic background, no thermalization is observed as these are still few-body problems in a subspace with subexponential scaling with system size [55][56][57].",
    "We will start by illustrating these behaviors using numerical simulations to provide a comprehensive basis for our study.",
    "We further consider the addition of diagonal disorder seen by the conduction electron.",
    "As expected, Anderson localization leads to an additional suppression of thermalization."
  ],
